value.0: A crystal glimmering with electrical energies.
A crystal hangs from the wall, glimmering with arcane energies.

I pray to Eldath everyday for forgiveness. We only pray the price for the sins we have committed. Our fears had gotten the better of us, should we have revolted would end in our death- something I would have gladly accepted if I knew the consequences. I hear rumours that Jarl Blackmoor demands more of our work, that we would become subjects to his experiments. To work eternally, lay bricks and build this hell of an abyss. Damned into this keep until one would save us. A fate worse than death that some would end their lives before it could happen.

Many of us are Fathers to our loved ones, yet we know that we will never see them. At least some had been spared from the cursed windmill, though our sins lay bare as we tossed one innocent to another, watching their bones and flesh grind into mortar. Few have escaped, though tradegy winds in one way or another, as the rumours suggest. 

The men here rabble amongst one another, fighting for the rations we have left. There is no hope further.

~ Ulfer Tosman

Lord Blackmoor has ordered the experiments of his hounds in the Kennel's below. Each of them seem to have their uses. The general Hounds of the swamp complement as any tracker's companion. The two headed-hounds are a rare breed of siamese hounds, tampered and mated with hellhounds of the abyss. These ones are vicious, though like the swamp hounds, tend to be quite... obedient. Blackmoor often had to controll the minds of these creatures whenever they acted up.

The skeletal hounds are somewhat disturbing. Bashing a hound with a club, mace or what have you is effective for loosening them up. Perhaps these experiments need more work.

~ Kennel Master J. Grenborg

Ulfer, if you want to destroy the magic crystals, toss something hard and heavy. Don't get too close to it.

~ P. Axel
A crystal brimming with arcane energies ready to strike. Perhaps worth smashing, in a way that won't harm you!
Projectile Trap Trigger, Delayed Blast Fireball (Fatal)
*Upon entering, you immediately smell the stench of rotting flesh. Corpses are hung against the pillars with nooses around their necks.*
*This appears to be a safe area to rest, as long as the door is closed...*
